The release of curcumin from its encapsulation in CsNPs was performed at pH 7.4, and the nanoparticles were re-dispersed in PBS. The total volume of the solution was divided into 5 tubes at 37°C under orbital shaking. Subsequently, curcumin in nanoparticles was centrifuged at 966 × g for 10 minutes, where the sediment was extracted in methanol and quantified using spectrophotometry. Finally, the release of curcumin from CsNPs was quantified according to the following equation:
